sentences: Gimel Androus Keaton (born February 27, 1974), better known by his stage name Young Guru, is an American audio engineer, record producer, disc jockey, and record executive from Wilmington, Delaware.
In 2019, Young Guru won a Grammy Award for Best Urban Contemporary Album for mixing the album Everything Is Love by The Carters.
He began DJing in Washington DC in 1996, where he met singer/rapper Nonchalant, who had a top 20 single at the time, and became her tour DJ.
In 1999, Young Guru went independent and moved to New York, where he worked with Deric "D-Dot" Angelettie on his Madd Rapper project and with Memphis Bleek.
The Throne' world tour featuring Jay-Z and Kanye West, and also for JAY-Z's '4:44' TourIn August 2013, Young Guru taught an audio mixing class via Skillshare.

In November 2018, Young Guru was credited with mixing the latest Meek Mill album Championships.
